      <intermediateExchange id="ef0481e3-c561-5c10-abc7-a93d837c4eb3" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="1310-73-2" amount="0.06888403587076286" intermediateExchangeId="61396bcb-bf35-411a-a6a6-8543ccef83e8" activityLinkId="0ff14b6a-8dcf-508f-a340-73733d530fd5">
        <name xml:lang="en">sodium hydroxide, without water, in 50% solution state</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
39.997108g/mol is the molar mass of sodium hydroxide, without water, in 50% solution state (HNaO). 
163.940666g/mol is the molar mass of trisodium phosphate (Na3O4P). 

Trisodium phosphate is modelled here as the product of the reaction of phosphoric acid with sodium hydroxide (Schrödter 2008).
Chemical reaction:
3NaOH + H3PO4 -&gt; Na3PO4 + 3 H2O
Sodium hydroxide can be substituted with NaOCl, NaCL, NaNO3 (Schrödter 2008).</comment>
